title: Brink Proposal #1: Request an order type
body:
Brink allows users to sign transactions that will automatically execute when certain conditions are met. All transactions in Brink are gas-deferred, they are free to create and you don’t pay a gas cost until the transaction is fully executed.

We will be launching Brink with a couple of basic order execution types, but decided it would be best to ask the community which order types they'd most like to see added after launch.

The options are as follows:

1. Automatic Dollar Cost Averaging: Pick any asset you want to DCA into. For example, you can set an order to convert 500 DAI to UNI every 14 days. 
2. Stop-loss Order: Set a stop-loss order for any asset.  For example, sell 5 ETH if the price of ETH drops below 2000 USDC. 
3. Uniswap V3 LP Automated Entry/Exit: Automatically exit or enter a Uniswap V3 LP position based on the LP's value.  For example, automatically sell 50% of a ETH/UNI LP position if the value of the position reaches 10,000 USDC
